  "prompt": "Why does Balaji Vishwanathan not make YouTube videos to spread his knowledge so people can learn more from it?",
  "response": "Balaji Vishwanathan, a well-known entrepreneur and writer, has chosen various platforms to share his knowledge and insights, such as writing detailed answers on Quora, producing articles, and through his companies and products. There could be several reasons he might not prioritize creating YouTube videos:\n\n1. **Preference for Written Content**: Some people prefer expressing their thoughts and sharing knowledge through written content rather than video. Writing allows for precise articulation and detailed explanation of complex topics.\n\n2. **Time Constraints**: As an entrepreneur and CEO, Balaji might have limited time to produce video content, which can be more time-consuming compared to writing.\n\n3. **Audience Engagement**: He may have found that his target audience engages more effectively with his written content on platforms like Quora, where he has a significant following.\n\n4. **Expertise**: Balaji has established expertise and a robust presence in written and product-based formats and might prefer to continue focusing on these areas where he excels.\n\n5. **Resource Allocation**: Producing high-quality video content requires resources such as equipment, editing skills, and possibly a team. Balaji might choose to allocate his resources to areas he finds more impactful or aligned with his goals.\n\nUltimately, the choice of platform depends on personal preference, strategic decisions, and the nature of the audience engagement. While he might not be active on YouTube in the form of videos, he continues to share substantial knowledge through other means.",
